In [[Greek mythology]], '''Calybe''' ([[Ancient Greek]]: Καλυβη means "rustic hut") was a [[nymph]] who was a wife of the [[Troy|Trojan]] king [[Laomedon]] and the mother of [[Bucolion]]. <ref>[[Pseudo-|Pseudo]]-[[Apollodorus of Athens|Apollodorus]]. ''[[Bibliotheca (Pseudo-Apollodorus)|Bibliotheca]], [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Apollod.+3.12.3&fromdoc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.01.0022 3.12.3]''</ref>

