[[Image:Limited Run Quilt Maple.jpg|thumb|Quilted maple back & side <br/>on Gibson Dove 1 of 20]]

'''Quilt''' or '''quilted maple''' refers to a type of [[Figure_(wood)|figure]] in [[maple]] wood. It is seen on the tangential plane (flat-sawn) and looks like a wavy "quilted" pattern, often similar to ripples on water. The quilted figure is only found in the Western Big Leaf species of maple {{dubious|date=February 2018}}. It is a distortion of the grain pattern itself. Prized for its beauty, it is used frequently in the manufacturing of [[musical instrument]]s, especially guitars. Quilted maple is an end grain figure that shows a circular pattern on flat sawn material. There are many terms that describe the shape and pattern of quilted maple, such as watered, popcorn, tubular, sausage, bubble wrap, and angle step.



