{{About|the nature park in Kars Province|the national park in Ankara Province|Soğuksu National Park}} {{Infobox protected area | name = Soğuksu Nature Park | alt_name = Soğuksu Tabiat Parkı | iucn_category = | photo = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | photo_width = | map = Turkey | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | relief = yes | label = Soğuksu Nature Park | label_position = left | mark = | marker_size = | location = [[Sarıkamış]], [[Kars Province]], Turkey | nearest_city = [[Sarıkamış]] |||||| | coords = {{coord|40|18|36|N|42|38|05|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | area = {{convert|11|ha|acre|abbr=on}} | designation = | authorized = | created = | established = 2011 | designated = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = [[Ministry of Forest and Water Management (Turkey)|Ministry of Forest and Water Management]] | administrator = | operator = | owner = | world_heritage_site = | website = | url = | child = | embedded = }} '''Soğuksu Nature Park''' ({{lang-tr|Soğuksu Tabiat Parkı}}), established in 2011, is a [[nature park]] in [[Eastern Anatolia Region]] of Turkey. It is located {{convert|53|km|mi|abbr=on}} far from [[Kars]] and {{convert|3|km|mi|abbr=on}} to [[Sarıkamış]].<ref name="b13osib"/>
The nature park covers an area of {{convert|11|ha|acres|abbr=on}} at {{convert|2121|-|2152|m|ft|abbr=on}} above main sea level.<ref name="b13osib"/>
==Geology== The area in and around of the nature park consists of [[basalt]] and [[dolomite]] rocks of [[Tertiary]] and [[Quaternary]] [[geologic time scale|period]]s. Additionally, [[tuff]], [[conglomerate (geology)|conglomerate]] and [[breccia]] are present.<ref name="b13osib"/>
==Flora== The nature park features forest stand of [[Scots pine]] (''Pinus sylvestris''). In the areas between the forest stands, [[quaking aspen]] (''Populus tremula'') grow. Othercommon plants are [[rose hip]] and [[buttercup]] (''Ranunculus acris'').<ref name="b13osib"/>
==Climate== The climate in the park shows characteristics of harsh continental climate. Long lasting winters are snowy, frostyand very cold. In winter time, more precipitation falls than in the summer period. The highest precipitation occurs just before the summer begins.<ref name="b13osib"/>
